---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageCard from '../components/PageCard.astro';

// Related pages
const relatedPages = [
  { 
    title: "Main Baseplate",
    description: "The primary baseplate that serves as the foundation of the game.",
    url: "/main-baseplate",
    icon: "baseplate"
  },
  { 
    title: "Prestige Points",
    description: "Learn about the next tier of currency after Points.",
    url: "/prestige-points",
    icon: "currency"
  },
  { 
    title: "Points Baseplate",
    description: "Discover the specialized baseplate dedicated to Points optimization.",
    url: "/points-baseplate",
    icon: "baseplate"
  }
];
---

<Layout title="Points" description="Information about Points - the primary currency in the game." currentPage="Points">
  <article class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Points</h1>
    
    <div class="bg-neutral-100 dark:bg-neutral-800 p-4 rounded-lg mb-8">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400 text-sm mb-2">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
          <polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"></polyline>
        </svg>
        Last updated: April 10, 2025
      </div>
      <p class="text-neutral-800 dark:text-neutral-200 font-medium">
        Points are the primary currency in the game, used for purchasing upgrades and unlocking new features.
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What Are Points?</h2>
    <p>
      Points are the fundamental currency of the game. They are generated automatically at a base rate, which can be increased through various upgrades, achievements, and mechanics. Points are required for nearly all early game progression and continue to be important throughout your journey.
    </p>
    
    <div class="my-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
      <div class="flex-1 bg-neutral-100 dark:bg-neutral-800 p-4 rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Base Generation</h3>
        <p class="text-sm">
          Initial production rate: 1 Point/second<br>
          Can be increased through upgrades and multipliers
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex-1 bg-neutral-100 dark:bg-neutral-800 p-4 rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Point Cap</h3>
        <p class="text-sm">
          Starting cap: 100 Points<br>
          Increases with specific upgrades and achievements
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex-1 bg-neutral-100 dark:bg-neutral-800 p-4 rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Offline Gain</h3>
        <p class="text-sm">
          Starts at 0% of online production<br>
          Can be improved through the Offline Baseplate
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Point Generation Methods</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-medium">Passive Generation</h3>
      <p>
        The most basic form of Point generation is passive production. Your base generation rate is influenced by:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 ml-6 list-disc">
        <li>Base multiplier (increases with upgrades)</li>
        <li>Achievement bonuses</li>
        <li>Special events multipliers</li>
        <li>Prestige bonuses</li>
        <li>Transcension effects</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-6">Active Methods</h3>
      <p>
        Besides passive generation, there are several active ways to earn Points:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 ml-6 list-disc">
        <li><strong>Clicking:</strong> Manually clicking the Point button provides Points based on your click power</li>
        <li><strong>Challenges:</strong> Completing challenges can reward large Point bonuses</li>
        <li><strong>Mining:</strong> The mining system allows for resource gathering that can be converted to Points</li>
        <li><strong>Achievements:</strong> One-time bonuses for reaching milestones</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Points Formula</h2>
    <div class="bg-neutral-100 dark:bg-neutral-800 p-4 rounded-lg my-4 font-mono text-sm overflow-x-auto">
      <p>Base Points per Second = 1 × (1 + Basic Multiplier) × (1 + Achievement Multiplier) × Prestige Multiplier × Transcension Multiplier</p>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400 mt-2">
      This formula represents the standard calculation for Points generation. Additional factors may apply based on unlocked features.
    </p>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Upgrade Path</h2>
    <p>
      The most efficient path for upgrading your Points generation is:
    </p>
    
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-4">
      <table class="w-full border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-neutral-100 dark:bg-neutral-800">
            <th class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2 text-left">Priority</th>
            <th class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2 text-left">Upgrade</th>
            <th class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2 text-left">Cost</th>
            <th class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2 text-left">Effect</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">1</td>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">Basic Generator</td>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">10 Points</td>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">+1 Point/sec</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800/50">
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">2</td>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">Improved Efficiency</td>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">50 Points</td>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">×2 multiplier to all generation</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">3</td>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">Capacity Expansion</td>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">100 Points</td>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">×5 Point cap</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800/50">
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">4</td>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">Automation Basics</td>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">250 Points</td>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">25% offline production</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">5</td>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">Advanced Generator</td>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">500 Points</td>
            <td class="border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 px-4 py-2">+5 Points/sec</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Advanced Strategies</h2>
    
    <div class="bg-primary-50 dark:bg-primary-900/20 border border-primary-200 dark:border-primary-800 p-4 rounded-lg my-6">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-primary-800 dark:text-primary-200 mb-2">Exponential Growth Strategy</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
        Once you reach 1,000 Points, consider performing your first Prestige. This will reset your Points but provide a permanent multiplier to all future Point generation. The formula for determining the optimal time to Prestige is:
      </p>
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-800 p-3 rounded mt-2 font-mono text-sm">
        Optimal Prestige Point = √(current Points × 10)
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="bg-accent-50 dark:bg-accent-900/20 border border-accent-200 dark:border-accent-800 p-4 rounded-lg my-6">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-accent-800 dark:text-accent-200 mb-2">Synergy Focus</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
        After unlocking multiple Baseplates, focus on upgrades that provide synergistic bonuses between systems. For example, the "Cross-System Amplifier" upgrade provides a multiplier based on the number of active Baseplates you have.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
  
  <section class="mt-12 border-t border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800 pt-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Related Pages</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      {relatedPages.map(page => (
        <PageCard 
          title={page.title} 
          description={page.description} 
          url={page.url}
          icon={page.icon}
        />
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>